    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Kyle Tucker**, who commands an elite score of 85.90. His matchup against Feltner is ideal, benefiting from a 14% park boost and significant SP skill advantage. **Gunnar Henderson** follows closely with an 81.76 score, buoyed by a prime leadoff spot and a strong platoon edge. However, **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s start carries a 31% rain risk, which we will monitor closely. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** also projects as a top-tier play (73.66); his dynamic platoon advantage (+14%) against Houser makes him a standout option to anchor the middle infield, while **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages** earn strong ratings\u201471.68 and 72.64, respectively\u2014thanks to the slow delivery of M\u00e1rquez, which significantly enhances their stolen base potential, a critical metric for our roster strategy.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Nasim Nunez**, who fell just short of the starting cut with a 57.95 efficiency score. While **Nasim Nunez** offers the switch-hitting versatility and speed we value, the optimizer prioritized the higher power-weighted production of **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.98) and **Nolan Schanuel** (62.47). We are exercising caution with **Jackson Merrill**, whose score of 55.68 is suppressed by a negative platoon split against Kikuchi and the presence of an elite defensive catcher. Elsewhere, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a locked-in start at 64.56, and **Miguel Vargas** earns a start at 64.64, largely fueled by a favorable 10% park boost and the exploitable pitching profile of Severino. We advise keeping a close watch on **Coby Mayo** and the aforementioned **Gunnar Henderson** as late-afternoon lineups finalize and weather reports update.",
